<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="1064" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[163,780,938,1052]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1064">
<emphasis box="[163,289,938,959]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1064">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name is derived from the Latin 
<taxonomicName box="[700,773,939,960]" class="Lobosa" family="Arcellidae" genus="Galeripora" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Arcellinida" pageId="20" pageNumber="1064" phylum="Amoebozoa" rank="species" species="sitiens">
<emphasis box="[700,773,939,960]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1064">sitiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, dry or thirsty. We propose this name because the habitat of this species is characterized by prolonged drought with episodic rainfall.
</paragraph>
